trans-unit.source: Team Foundation Server
trans-unit.target: Team Foundation Server

trans-unit.source: An enterprise-grade server for teams to share code, track work, and ship software — for any language, all in a single package.
trans-unit.target: An enterprise-grade server for teams to share code, track work, and ship software — for any language, all in a single package.

trans-unit.source: It’s the perfect complement to your IDE.
trans-unit.target: It’s the perfect complement to your IDE.

trans-unit.source: Learn more about Team Foundation Server
trans-unit.target: Learn more about Team Foundation Server

trans-unit.source: With Team Foundation Server, you license the server and the users connecting to the server.
trans-unit.target: With Team Foundation Server, you license the server and the users connecting to the server.

trans-unit.source: Users who only need access to work items are free, and other users need a user CAL (client access license) for access to most features in Team Foundation Server.
trans-unit.target: Users who only need access to work items are free, and other users need a user CAL (client access license) for access to most features in Team Foundation Server.

trans-unit.source: Each Visual Studio subscription includes a server license and one user CAL for Team Foundation Server, making this one of the best ways to acquire Team Foundation Server.
trans-unit.target: Each Visual Studio subscription includes a server license and one user CAL for Team Foundation Server, making this one of the best ways to acquire Team Foundation Server.

trans-unit.source: You can also acquire TFS CALs by purchasing users in your Visual Studio Team Services account.
